Corrections  Amplifications
---
   HONDA MOTOR Co. of Japan projects that net income will
fall 17% in the fiscal year ending March 31, to 63.1 billion
yen ($485.7 million), while sales will rise 3% to 4.428
trillion yen. In last Thursday's edition, the forecast was
misstated.
   (See: "International Brief -- Honda Motor Co.: Quarterly
Pretax Earnings Fell 24%; Sales Rose 2.8%" -- WSJ Feb. 20,
1992)
   ---
   DIESEL TECHNOLOGY Co. is 51%-owned by Penske
Transportation Inc. of Detroit and 49%-owned by a U.S. unit
of Robert Bosch G.m.b.H. of Germany. The division of
ownership in the joint venture was reported incorrectly in
yesterday's edition.
   (See: "International: Bosch Unit Buys Stake" -- WSJ Feb.
26, 1992)